					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445463#post-4696354</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445463/scp-5082#post-4696354</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2020 06:52:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Petrograd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>455145</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Ok, goddamnit, +1. The imagery in many places was quite interesting, and those couple of wham lines (you make us look like the bad guys, I don't know how to fix a god, we've got a war to win), just&#8230;. wham.</p> <p>I was holding onto my novote for quite a while there, though. The main problem is that you're often un-economical with your writing, particularly when writing in clinical tone. You're very often repeating details we've read one or two paragraphs back. This also happens every time you start a new document, section, or log, where things would <em>logically</em> be repeated in a real document, but <em>I've already read it once, I get it</em>. You've already got a <em>lot</em> of narrative and imagery that you're asking us to work through, don't make me feel like you're wasting my time when there is cool stuff to get to.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
